      "comment": "Leaning to VEGA VIXEN (3) in the opener off a professional debut win at Caulfield Heath over 1000m, sitting up on speed and kicking off a genuine tempo to win well. Fancy she beat a couple of handy ones there and up to 1100m will pose no issue. Expect her to prove very hard to run down again. DIVINE DOT (1) has done nothing wrong in winning both starts this time in, the latest at Sandown Hillside when up on speed. Can give a sight again. RESONANT (2) struggled out to 1400m here last time, the debut over this distance was good and he can bounce back. PROFUMO (5) is a Home Affairs colt on debut for the Hayes yard who can run well.",
